<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFF9FFDE0DF10E7D0743D0F0" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFF9FFDE0DF10E7D0288D065" blockId="39.[151,1437,1578,2001]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0DF10E7D0746D13C" bold="true" box="[151,274,1578,1604]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF9FFDE0CF50E7C0463D13D" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" box="[403,567,1579,1605]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0CF50E7C0463D13D" box="[403,567,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Siderolamprus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have (1) claw sheath, absent, (2) contact between the nasal and rostral scales, present or absent, (3) scales in contact with the nasal scale, six, (4) postnasal scales, two, (5) position of the nostril in the nasal scale, posterior, (6) keels on dorsal body scales, present or absent, (7) digits per limb, five, (8) longest toe lamellae, 14–35, (9) dorsal scale rows, 65–85, (10) relative head width, 9.88–15.6, (11) relative rostral height, 44.7–63.9, (12) relative frontonasal length, 2.46–2.88, (13) relative interparietal distance, 0.561–1.14, (14) relative axilla-groin distance, 53.5–65.3. From 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF9FFDE0F290E8804A6D180" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[591,754,1759,1784]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Mesoamericus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0F290E8804A6D180" box="[591,754,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Mesoamericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0F9D0E880531D181" bold="true" box="[763,869,1759,1785]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFF9FFDE0F9D0E880531D181" box="[763,869,1759,1785]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, we distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF9FFDE09780E880296D181" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" box="[1054,1218,1759,1785]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE09780E880296D181" box="[1054,1218,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Siderolamprus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the claw sheath (absent versus present in 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF9FFDE0CD40F540401D064" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[434,597,1795,1820]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Mesoamericus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="39" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0CD40F540401D064" box="[434,597,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Mesoamericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and relative rostral height (44.7–63.9 versus 65.0–67.0).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52700B06FFF9FFDE0DA10F710743D0F0" blockId="39.[151,1437,1578,2001]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF9FFDE0DA10F71077BD038" bold="true" box="[199,303,1830,1856]" pageId="39" pageNumber="240">Content.</emphasis>
Fourteen species (
<tableCitation id="1F4D3EBDFFF9FFDE0F6D0F700432D039" box="[523,614,1831,1857]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="14.[151,239,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,1404,2011]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 3. Classification and distribution of lizards of the family Diploglossidae (55 species). For common names we use modifying words from literature sources, in some cases modified for consistency following guidelines (Hedges et al. 2019). The IUCN Redlist threat status is indicated in parentheses (NA = not assessed)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/06B05B8EFFD0FFF70DF10D5C0264D214" pageId="39" pageNumber="240" tableUuid="06B05B8EFFD0FFF70DF10D5C0264D214">Table 3</tableCitation>
