<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFF4FFD30DA108C0028AD7AE" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFF4FFD30DA108C0028AD7AE" blockId="42.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30DA108C0071AD7C9" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is from the Greek 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30E6108C00503D7C9" box="[775,855,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">sideros</emphasis>
(iron) and 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30EBB08C0026CD7C9" box="[989,1080,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">lampros</emphasis>
(bright, radiant), apparently in allusion to “glossy black” color of the 
<typeStatus id="8D74B5A4FFF4FFD30F2108EC0423D7AD" box="[583,631,187,213]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">type</typeStatus>
species, noted in the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="365E76F7FFF4FFD3093708EC0285D7AE" author="Cope, E. D." box="[1105,1233,187,214]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" pagination="368 - 374" refId="ref21700" refString="Cope, E. D. (1861) Descriptions of reptiles from tropical America and Asia. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 12, 368 - 374." type="journal article" year="1861">Cope 1861</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFF4FFD30DA1088806A4D6F1" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFF4FFD30DA1088806A4D6F1" blockId="42.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30DA10888076FD781" bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30C24088807B2D781" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" box="[322,486,223,249]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30C24088807B2D781" box="[322,486,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Siderolamprus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monophyletic clade with a support value of 100% in Bayesian and ML analyses (
<figureCitation id="CAF41783FFF4FFD30DC6095406B2D665" box="[160,230,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1748,1772]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,181,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[175,1412,181,1725]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Phylogenetic tree of diploglossid lizards based on sequences of nine genes: four mitochondrial genes (CytB, ND2, 12S rRNA, and 16S rRNA) and five nuclear genes (AMEL, BDNF, PLPR, RAG1, and ZFP36). Maximum likelihood tree obtained from the nine-gene dataset (59 individuals; 6,949 sites).A scale bar indicates 5% sequence divergence. The numbers at nodes are ML bootstrap values, followed by Bayesian posterior probabilities; asterisks indicate significant (≥ 95%) support, and a dash or zero value indicates weak (&lt;50%) support. The tree is rooted with Pseudopus apodus (Anguidae)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775446/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Our phylogenetic tree includes five of the 14 species of 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30E1809540276D665" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" box="[894,1058,259,285]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30E1809540276D665" box="[894,1058,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Siderolamprus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30952095407C1D639" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30952095402E9D665" authority="Cope, 1860" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1076,1213,259,285]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bivittatus">S. bivittatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD309AF0954032ED665" authority="Cope, 1860" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1225,1402,259,285]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyanochloris">S. cyanochloris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD308E109540711D638" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="enneagrammus">S. enneagrammus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30C34097007C5D639" authority="Cope, 1860" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1860" box="[338,401,295,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laf">S. laf</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30CB609700413D639" authority="Cope, 1860" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[464,583,295,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rozellae">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30CB609700413D639" box="[464,583,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">S. rozellae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The high levels of divergence (with some splits as old as 8 Mya) within the species 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFF4FFD30C7C091C0424D61C" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" box="[282,624,331,357]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Siderolamprus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="enneagrammus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFF4FFD30C7C091C0424D61C" box="[282,624,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Siderolamprus enneagrammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="CAF41783FFF4FFD30FE6091C0497D61D" box="[640,707,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1680,1704]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1655]" captionTargetId="figure-26@10.[152,1436,181,1656]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Timetree of Diploglossidae based on sequences of nine genes: four mitochondrial genes (CytB, ND2, 12S rRNA, and 16S rRNA) and five nuclear genes (AMEL, BDNF, PLPR, RAG1, and ZFP36). Nodes show divergence times in millions of years. A scale bar indicates time (6 million years ago, Mya). We show Bayesian credibility ranges as gray bars at nodes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775450/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="243">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) suggest that it is a complex that includes at least one undefined species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
